HEADWORD: Supplicat
<hw>Sup"pli*cat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., he
supplicates.]</ety> <fld>(Eng. Universities)</fld> <def>A petition;
esp., a written one, with a certificate that the conditions have been
complied with.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

